benchmark
------------------------------------------
A library to support the benchmarking of functions, similar to unit-tests.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libbenchmark-devel-1.9.5-1bl1
  libbenchmark1-1.9.5-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libgmock-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  libgtest-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  python39-3.9.16-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/google/benchmark

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/google/benchmark/archive/refs/tags/v1.9.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack benchmark-1.9.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./benchmark-1.9.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/benchmark-1.9.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/benchmark-1.9.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbenchmark1-1.9.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbenchmark-devel-1.9.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

